OL,6,F"When the network remains saturated
OL,7,Ffor this length of time, water
OL,8,Fpenetrates small cracks in the road
OL,9,Fsurface, the layers beneath weaken,
OL,10,Fpassing traffic forces the damaged
OL,11,Fsurface to break apart and potholes
OL,12,Fform more rapidly and more frequently
OL,13,Fthan under normal conditions.
OL,15,F"This cycle has been repeating since
OL,16,Fmid-December due to the prolonged wet
OL,17,Fweather, accelerating the rate at
OL,18,Fwhich defects develop."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/8
