OL,6,F"As a result, there will be delays to
OL,7,Fsome routine responses, inspections,
OL,8,Fand non-urgent repairs over the coming
OL,9,Fweeks.
OL,11,F"Once the network can dry out and
OL,12,Fstabilise, the rate of new pothole
OL,13,Fformation will reduce, enabling teams
OL,14,Fto make steady progress on the backlog
OL,15,Fover the next few weeks."
OL,17,FAndy Firbank sees the impact of
OL,18,Fpotholes by working at Wheel Surgery
OL,19,Fin Leeds.
